# Optional: GitHub OAuth App client_id baked into the build.
#
# Why: lets users sign in by clicking "Sign in with GitHub" in Settings
# without having to register their own OAuth App. The maintainer creates
# ONE OAuth App at github.com/settings/applications/new (toggle
# "Enable Device Flow" on), copies the Client ID below, then runs
# `bun run build`.
#
# Leave empty (or omit the file) and the extension falls back to the
# per-user override field in Settings → "Advanced — Override OAuth
# Client ID". Either path stores the resulting access_token in the
# same SecretStore.githubToken slot.
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
